This paper is about headline generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper discusses the task of controlling the length of headlines, which is a common problem in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of corpora and evaluation methods, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE).
